modules.description: This module establishes WebSocket connections and processes Gremlin queries with support for single and batch execution. It handles communication using `Websocket.Frame.t` and returns results as JSON, with detailed error handling for invalid responses or unmatched request IDs. It is used to interact with Gremlin-compatible graph databases over WebSocket, enabling query submission and transaction management.

This module provides functions to establish WebSocket connections and execute Gremlin queries, supporting both single and batch operations. It works with `Websocket.Frame.t` for communication and returns results in JSON format, including detailed error handling for invalid responses and unmatched request IDs. It is used to interact with Gremlin-compatible graph databases, enabling query submission and transaction management over WebSocket.
